The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 January is 28,579 (3,307.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 January, there were 5,537 new confirmed cases (640.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 January, there were 5,899 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 6% (362 fewer cases).
